# Introduction to E2E Testing

This is a test article about end-to-end testing in browser extensions.

questionsAnswers.question: What is E2E testing?
questionsAnswers.answer: End-to-end testing is a methodology used to test whether the flow of an application is performing as designed from start to finish.

questionsAnswers.question: Why use E2E testing for browser extensions?
questionsAnswers.answer: E2E testing ensures that browser extensions work correctly in real browser environments with actual user workflows.
